entries.femaleVariant: So we're eatin', right, and suddenly I look at her and I feel nothing. Like, zero emotion. It's as if she were a total rando.
And I-- I don't got anythin' to say, so I just sit there like a gonk and give her this fake-ass smile.
Just end it. You're lying to her and yourself. How long've you two been together?
Exactly. You've taken up enough of her time already. And don't you dare tell me, "It's not that simple." 'Cause it really is.
But... what if I can't be alone?
